Your web server configuration file /etc/nginx/nginx.conf has a syntax error causing the
server to fail on restart. Explain how you would open and edit this file using the vi 
editor. Detail the steps for navigating to the specific line containing the error, making 
the correction, saving your changes, and quitting vi. What commands would you use during 
the editing process?

Steps: 

1. Use the vi command 
    command : sudo vi /etc/nginx/nginx.conf

2. Search for keywords and navigate to the error line
    command : /

3. Quit and save if needed
    command : :q to quit and wq! to quit and save

4. Validate syntax
    command : nginx -t

5. After successful test, restart Nginx 
    command : sudo systemctl restart nginx
